The '''John von Neumann Environmental Research Institute of the Pacific''' is a [[non profit organization|non profit]] [[Environment (biophysical)|environmental]] and [[anthropological]] [[research institute]] of [[List of entities in the executive branch of Colombia|executive branch of the government]] of [[Colombia]] ascribed to the [[Ministry of Environment and Sustainable Development (Colombia)|Ministry of Environment and Sustainable Development]] and charged with conducting research and investigations on the [[Pacific]] [[littoral]] and the [[biodiversity]] of the [[Tumbes-Chocó-Magdalena|Chocó]] [[biogeographic]] [[Biodiversity hotspot|hotspot]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.humboldt.org.co/sina/sina-neumann.htm |title=Instituto de investigaciones ambientales del pacífico |publisher=[[Alexander von Humboldt Biological Resources Research Institute]] |accessdate=2010-11-11 |language=Spanish |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110707053605/http://www.humboldt.org.co/sina/sina-neumann.htm |archivedate=2011-07-07 |df= }}</ref>

